{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuring your user’s device ID with "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Customize Behavior","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/BrazeDelegate","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/overrideResourceBundle"],"anchor":"Customize-Behavior","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BrazeKit"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can be identified using one of two device ID options:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uidevice\/1620059-identifierforvendor","isActive":true},{"text":" property.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A randomly generated UUID."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifierForVendor"},{"type":"text","text":" may not be available in all scenarios or devices, Braze provides the option to use a more generic UUID to identify a user’s device."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Setting Your Configuration","anchor":"Setting-Your-Configuration"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To configure this option, set "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Braze.Configuration"},{"text":". Assigning this property to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" will generate a random UUID for each user installation, whereas a value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" will notify the SDK to use the device’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifierForVendor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let configuration = Braze.Configuration(","    apiKey: \"<BRAZE_API_KEY>\",","    endpoint: \"<BRAZE_ENDPOINT>\"",")","\/\/ Set this value to `true` to opt out of `identifierForVendor` usage.","configuration.useUUIDAsDeviceId = true","let braze = Braze(configuration: configuration)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting in 7.0.0, the default value for this property is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For device types that do not support "},{"code":"identifierForVendor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", such as watchOS or macOS, Braze will default to a randomly generated UUID regardless of which option is configured.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After being generated, device IDs created from UUIDs will remain consistent throughout the lifetime of the application’s installation or until ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/wipeData()","isActive":true},{"text":" is called.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since calling ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/wipeData()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will erase all local SDK storage, the device ID that was previously stored will be deleted. Thus, if "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is enabled, the SDK will generate a new UUID for the device ID after this operation. Similarly, if "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is disabled, the SDK will re-use the same IDFV after this operation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Migrating from a Previous Version","anchor":"Migrating-from-a-Previous-Version"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are migrating your project from the legacy "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Appboy\/appboy-ios-sdk"},{"type":"text","text":" or from a version of the Braze Swift SDK prior to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"5.7.0"},{"text":", note that the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifierForVendor"},{"type":"text","text":" option will be used by default, regardless of the configuration setting. This ensures continuity for any anonymous users previously identified by the "},{"code":"identifierForVendor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" device ID.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In such cases, if you wish to override those pre-existing values and ensure that your "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Configuration-swift.class\/useUUIDAsDeviceId"},{"type":"text","text":" configuration is respected, call "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/wipeData()","isActive":true},{"text":" on the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Braze"},{"text":" instance after migrating to any version of the Braze Swift SDK from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"5.7.0"},{"text":" onwards.","type":"te